The White House Office of the Press Secretary announced that President Obama will host the Nuclear Security Summit in April. The summit will include participation from 47 countries, as well as the United Nations, the IAEA, and the European Union. The President is also planning to host bilateral meetings with several world leaders, including the President of China, the Chancellor of Germany, and the Prime Minister of India. Additionally, the President will host a screening of the documentary film, Nuclear Tipping Point, which focuses on global nuclear dangers. The film features former Secretaries of State George Shultz and Henry Kissinger, former Secretary of Defense William Perry, and former Senator Sam Nunn.